        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 3:16PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 316 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Lincolnton, or 4 miles east of Cherryville, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gastonia, Bessemer City, High Shoals, Iron Station, and Crouse.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
